==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dys-
<hw>Dys-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>An inseparable prefix, fr. the Greek
<grk>dys-</grk> hard, ill, and signifying <sig>ill</sig>,
<sig>bad</sig>, <sig>hard</sig>, <sig>difficult</sig>, and the like; cf.
the prefixes, Skr. <xex>dus-</xex>, Goth. <xex>tuz-</xex>, OHG.
<xex>zur-</xex>, G. <xex>zer-</xex>, AS. <xex>to-</xex>, Icel.
<xex>tor-</xex>, Ir. <xex>do-</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dysaesthesia</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
